snippet.title: Egypt: El-Sissi in final step to run for president
snippet.description: Egypt's former military chief on Monday took the final formal step to run in next month's presidential election, submitting to the election commission eight times the number of signatures required, his campaign said in a statement.

snippet.title: Egypt military: Prominent militant killed in Sinai
snippet.description: Egypt's military said its forces on Friday killed a prominent Islamic militant in the Sinai Peninsula, part of a campaign against extremist groups that have carried out a string of attacks, bombings and assassinations on police and soldiers extending to the capital.

snippet.title: Dutch priest dubbed 'Syrian of Syrians' is assassinated at his monastery in Homs
snippet.description: After nearly 50 years in Syria, the priest had steadfastly refused to leave Homs.

snippet.title: Blasts near Cairo University kill Egyptian police official, injure five
snippet.description: Three bombs went off at a checkpoint Wednesday, the latest attack ahead of the Egyptian presidential election.

snippet.title: Still mad as hell after all these years
snippet.description: A new book rekindles our fated connection to the 1976 movie "Network."

snippet.title: Bomb explodes in Hezbollah-controlled area of Beirut, killing at least 4
snippet.description: The blast in a Hezbollah-controlled area is the latest sign of Lebanon's slide toward sectarian conflict.

snippet.title: Former Pakistan ruler defies court order
snippet.description: Pakistan's ex-ruler refused to appear in court on treason charges, saying his life was at risk.

snippet.title: Powerful explosion rocks downtown Beirut; former ambassador to U.S., 4 others killed
snippet.description: A huge blast caused multiple casualties Friday morning near a downtown hotel.

snippet.title: Egypt's military-backed government declares Muslim Brotherhood a terrorist organization
snippet.description: Government declaration is the latest significant blow to a group that was victorius in 2012 national election.

snippet.title: Hezbollah commander Hassan al-Laqees assassinated outside his Beirut home
snippet.description: Hezbollah blamed Israel for the assassination
